<p><strong>Objective</strong>: Standardize naming conventions across database tables and Result files to eliminate false positives in schema_compare page categorization.</p>
<p><strong>Root Cause</strong>: Result file table declarations are inconsistent - some follow Catalyst/DBIx::Class standards (snake_case) while others use all-lowercase without underscores, causing false positives in table-to-result-file matching.</p>

<h2>Problem Statement</h2>

<h3>Current Inconsistency</h3>

<ul>
<li>Result files use <strong>PascalCase</strong> filenames (e.g., <code>AiModelConfig.pm</code>, <code>CodeSearchIndex.pm</code>)</li>
<li>Result file table declarations are <strong>inconsistent</strong>:
  <ul>
  <li>Correct pattern: PascalCase file + proper snake_case declaration (e.g., <code>AiModelConfig.pm</code> → <code>ai_model_config</code>) ✓</li>
  <li>Broken pattern: PascalCase file + all-lowercase declaration (e.g., <code>CodeSearchIndex.pm</code> → <code>codesearchindex</code>) ✗</li>
  </ul>
</li>
<li>Database tables may not match Result file declarations</li>
<li>Schema compare page shows false positives ("Tables without Result Files") when declarations don't match actual table names</li>
</ul>

<h3>Root Cause Analysis</h3>

<p>Result file declarations do not follow consistent naming convention aligned with Catalyst/DBIx::Class standards. The application standard is: <strong>PascalCase filenames paired with snake_case table declarations</strong>. Currently, 4 Result files violate this by using all-lowercase declarations instead of proper snake_case.</p>

<h2>Proposed Solution</h2>

<p>Standardize all Result files to follow the <strong>established Catalyst/DBIx::Class convention</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Result file names</strong>: PascalCase (e.g., <code>AiModelConfig.pm</code>) ✓ Already correct</li>
<li><strong>Declared table names</strong>: snake_case (e.g., <code>ai_model_config</code>) - Fix 4 files</li>
<li><strong>Database table names</strong>: Match declared names exactly</li>
</ul>

<h3>Benefits of Standardization</h3>

<ul>
<li><strong>Eliminates Technical Debt</strong> - No workaround/normalization code needed</li>
<li><strong>Enforces Standards</strong> - Future developers follow established convention</li>
<li><strong>Reduces Bugs</strong> - Naming consistency prevents schema mismatch issues</li>
<li><strong>Simplifies Maintenance</strong> - Single naming rule instead of complex workarounds</li>
<li><strong>Improves Code Quality</strong> - Aligns with industry best practices for Catalyst/DBIx::Class</li>
<li><strong>Fixes Root Cause</strong> - Eliminates schema_compare false positives at source</li>
</ul>

<h2>Scope: Result Files Requiring Fix</h2>

<h3>Category A: Files with Non-Standard Declarations (Requires Fix)</h3>

<table border="1">
<tr>
<th>Result File</th>
<th>Current Declaration</th>
<th>Should Be (Standard)</th>
<th>Database Table</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>CodeSearchIndex.pm</code></td>
<td><code>codesearchindex</code></td>
<td><code>code_search_index</code></td>
<td><code>codesearchindex</code> (needs rename)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>DocumentationMetadataIndex.pm</code></td>
<td><code>documentationmetadataindex</code></td>
<td><code>documentation_metadata_index</code></td>
<td><code>documentationmetadataindex</code> (needs rename)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>WebSearchResult.pm</code></td>
<td><code>websearchresult</code></td>
<td><code>web_search_result</code></td>
<td><code>websearchresult</code> (needs rename)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
